    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-03T07:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-03T07:35:00-05:00" n="220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1956: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-03T16:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 3, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 3—3:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>412. Political situation continues to drift hopelessly. Relations between Majlis
                    and Government unimproved, most deputies continuing to play their game of
                    obstruction and opportunism. For example Budget Bill for year now nearing end
                    not yet passed. The Full Powers Bill was referred to committee without mention
                    of urgency.</p>
                <pb facs="0219" n="207" xml:id="pg_207"/>
                <p>Political intrigue against Qavam<note n="77" xml:id="d220fn77">Ahmad Qavam, Prime
                        Minister of Iran.</note> is increasing; leading candidates being mentioned
                    are Soheily<note n="78" xml:id="d220fn78">Ali Soheily, former Prime Minister of
                        Iran.</note> and Ali Mansour. Cabinet changes are imminent, principal one
                    being dismissal of Gharagozlou as Minister of Justice.</p>
                <p>It seems likely the rapidly developing food shortage will bring about new crisis
                    which will result in Qavam’s fall or dissolution of Majlis. There can be no
                    continuity or stability in Government as long as Majlis is composed of
                    irresponsible elements intent on pursuing their own interests.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
